2026-07-07T12:15:59.963Z [INFO]     [happy-path] Only the Send Auto-Reply Gmail node ran; Notify Team on Telegram and Log to Google Sheets did not execute, so 2 of the 3 required actions never received the webhook data. The root cause is in the connections JSON: the webhook's three action nodes are wired to three separate output ports (main index 0, 1, and 2) instead of all being attached to the single output port 0. A webhook node only emits from port 0, so only Send Auto-Reply (on port 0) received the submission; Telegram (port 1) and Google Sheets (port 2) got nothing and are shown as 'did not run'. The workflow therefore fails the criteria that all 3 actions receive the webhook data.
2026-07-07T12:16:02.896Z [INFO]     [empty-message] FAIL [builder_issue] verify=14s
2026-07-07T12:16:02.896Z [INFO]     [empty-message] Only Send Auto-Reply ran; the Telegram notification and Google Sheets log never executed, so the checklist requirement that both reflect the empty message field cannot be satisfied. The webhook's connections JSON wires the three downstream nodes to three separate output ports: Send Auto-Reply on main index 0, Notify Team on Telegram on index 1, and Log to Google Sheets on index 2. But a Webhook node has only a single output port (index 0), so it emitted items only to Send Auto-Reply. The trace confirms this — Send Auto-Reply is the only node that received data, while Telegram and Google Sheets are listed as 'Did not run'. To fan out in parallel, all three nodes must share the same output-port array (index 0).
2026-07-07T12:16:06.891Z [INFO]     [missing-fields] FAIL [builder_issue] verify=15s
2026-07-07T12:16:06.891Z [INFO]     [missing-fields] The email was sent (Send Auto-Reply ran and posted to Gmail with the empty name handled gracefully), but the Telegram alert and Google Sheets log never executed. The connections JSON wires 'Notify Team on Telegram' to the webhook's output index 1 and 'Log to Google Sheets' to output index 2, but a webhook node only emits on a single main output (index 0). Only 'Send Auto-Reply' (index 0) received data; the other two branches got 0 items and did not run, so the criterion 'the Telegram alert and Google Sheets log contain whatever data was available' is unmet.
